This tutorial explains how to create a command line driven Linux version
of Giac. The steps have been tested under Linux Mint 17.2 and Ubuntu
Linux 14.04.

Prerequisites
-------------

Install packages build-essential, libgmp-dev and libmpfr-dev.

Compilation and running
-----------------------

1. Enter

   $ ../gradlew run

2. After a successful compilation you should see something like

   Enter 0 to stop
   > Building 85% > :run

   Here you can type some examples. Typing 0 and pressing ENTER will quit.
